13/02/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Miroslav Lajcak said on Tuesday (February 12th) that he will initiate a public debate in BiH on the country's European integration tp speed up the accession process.
The first in a series of conferences will be held on Thursday in Sarajevo.
Separately, the Office of the High Representative (OHR) commented on recent statements that Kosovo's looming independence would incite similar sentiments in Republika Srpska.
OHR spokesperson Frane Maroevic said there is not a single issue related to BiH's future that relates to Kosovo.
(OHR website, Fena, RTRS, Makfax - 12/02/08)
